sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1444005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Composite promoter and consensus B. subtilis RBS - C2P22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
A composite part consisting of the constitutive promoter Pveg (BBa_K823003), followed by the repressible promoter C1P22(BBa_R0053), and ending with the consensus RBS from B. subtilis (BBa_K090505).
This composite part was intended to control the expression of a downstream reporter, regulated by the expression of the C2P22 repressor protein. The constitutive promoter Pveg allows reliable expression when the repressible promoter is not repressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Ziemianowicz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No interference with endogenous cell signalling.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K823003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Pveg is a strong, constitutive promoter of Bacillus subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Korinna Kraft

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cII p22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The p22 cII regulatory region sequence is a 97 base-pair sequence with the standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. p22 cII repressor protein, BBa_C0053, binds to it.
This segment contains O-R1, O-R2, a fragment of O-R3, the -35 of P-RM, and P-R (-10 and -35 from Tom Knight)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Maia Mahoney

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K090505
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the consensus RBS for Bacillus subtilis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Goodman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part must be 8 nucleotides away from the first methionine of the coding sequence, and so we added 'TGT' downstream of the actual binding sequence: AAAGGAGG. This, combined with the truncated non-CDS BioBrick prefix scar, gives exactly 8 'spacer bases' between the 3' end of the RBS and the start of the coding sequence.
